==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scaleboard
<hw>Scale"board`</hw> <pr>(?; <it>commonly</it> <?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[3d <ets>scale</ets> + <ets>board</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>A thin slip of wood used to justify a
page.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Crabb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A thin veneer of leaf of wood used for covering the
surface of articles of furniture, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Scaleboard plane</b></col>, <cd>a plane for cutting from
a board a wide shaving forming a scaleboard.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scaled</ent>⟦br⟧
